This paper is about generating conversation responses using sequence-to-sequence models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of self-attention and stochastic beam-search algorithm, which are common techniques in deep learning and artificial intelligence, respectively, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving the quality and diversity of responses, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of large datasets and mining data from the web, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges of generating long and coherent responses, which can be addressed using neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the fifth likely sub-category.
